HEADWORD: Aurelia
<hw>Au*re"li*a</hw> <pr>(?; 106)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
L. <ets>aurum</ets> gold: cf. F. <ets>aur⟦eacute⟧lie</ets>. Cf.
<er>Chrysalis</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The
chrysalis, or pupa of an insect, esp. when reflecting a brilliant golden
color, as that of some of the butterflies.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A
genus of jellyfishes. See <er>Discophora</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

